Unity Bank PLC’s half year 2019 results indicate that it grew its top line by 17 percent as revenue improved from N17.4 billion in half year  2018 to N20.5 billion in half year 2019 The bank recorded a growth in profitability by over 96% as its profit before tax stood at N1.052bn as against N536m in H1 2018. However, profit after tax stood at N967.5 million compared to N492 million in a similar period in 2018, which indicates a 96 percent growth. Earnings per share improved by 66% to 17.99kobo for the period ended June 30, 2019 compared to 10.86kobo in FY 2018; with PBT Margin, Net Assets per share and ROA improving by 1.3%, 0.2% and 0.2% respectively. Commenting on the result, the Managing Director/CEO, Mrs. Tomi Somefun said: “The Bank has started to reap from its multiple streams of income which include asset creation, investments and trade activities amongst others.”  2016: Naira devaluation takes toll on coys  half year  results FCMB sustains performance with N177.4bn revenue, achieves 73% profit increase Union Bank declares N12.1bn profit before tax in Half-year 2019 Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin